{{outlet}}
<div id="welcome-page" class="page">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="hero center">
      <h1>
        Visualisation tool for public spending data has arrived
      </h1>
      <p class="flow-text">
        Raw and dirty public spending data visualised into a sexy, tidy, filterable node network. That’s Elvis. He’s not finished yet, but if you are adventurous, try him out!
      </p>
      <br>
      <div>
          <a href="#" class="btn-large transparent hide">Use ready-made network</a>
            {{#link-to 'network.new' class="btn-large primary"}}Create a network{{/link-to}}
          {{#if session.isAuthenticated}}
          {{else}}
            {{#link-to 'account.new' class="btn-large primary"}}Create an account{{/link-to}}
          {{/if}}
      </div>
      <br>
      <br>
      <div class="node-types">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col s4 center-align">
            <div class="figure-buyer"></div>
            <h4>
              Governments
            </h4>
            <p class="small">
              Examine preferences of government institutions such as municipalities, ministries and others
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="col s4 center-align">
            <div class="figure-bidder"></div>
            <h4>bidders</h4>
            <p class="small">
              Discover which companies sell their goods and services to the governments
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="col s4 center-align">
            <div class="figure-relationship"></div>
            <h4>Contracts</h4>
            <p class="small">
              Dig into public contract details and money flows
            </p>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="full-width section-about">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col s12">
            <h1 class="big-title">
              A tool for revealing corruption
            </h1>
            <p class="flow-text big-content">
              Most of our tax money is spent through a process called tendering. Through these public tenders, private parties get hired to provide services for the country. There is a large body of data on public tenders.
            </p>
            <p>
              Use Elvis to visualise public spending in specific EU country, sector and year range. Reveal suspicious relationships between government and companies. Visually answer questions like
              "Who is dominatig IT market in Netherlands?" or "Which companies earn most money from public spending in Slovakia?"
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col m6">
            <h3 class="title">
              Under development
            </h3>
            <p class="content">
              Please be aware this is not a finish product. The core features are still under heavy developement. We are working on it and you are welcome to join us in developement or discuss your ideas.
            </p>
            <div class="links">
              <div class="link">
                <!--incont-->
                {{fa-icon 'smile-o'}}<a href="https://talk.tenders.exposed">Join the Elvis community</a>
              </div>
              <div class="link">
                {{fa-icon 'envelope-o'}}<a href="mailto:tech@tenders.exposed">Contact us</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col m6">
            <h3 class="title">
              Free and Open-source
            </h3>
            <p class="content">
              Elvis is developed as an open source tool and all code is published on GitHub. We are looking to creare a framework for the community to play with.
            </p>
            <div class="links">
              <div class="link">
                <!--incont-->
                {{fa-icon 'github'}}<a href="https://github.com/tenders-exposed">Elvis on GitHub</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col m6">
            <h3 class="title">
              Data source
            </h3>
            <p class="content">
              Currently we are using TED data for all network visualisations. Future plan is to provide custom and other data sources to work with.
            </p>
            <div class="links">
              <div class="link">
                <!--incont-->
                {{! {{fa-icon 'arrow-right'}\}<a href="#">About TED data</a> }}
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col m6">
            <h3 class="title">
              Based on research
            </h3>
            <p class="content">
              It's no mumbo-jumbo. There is an interesting research behind this idea. Learn about Red Flags and how we evaluate the data.
            </p>
            <div class="links">
              <div class="link">
                <!--incont-->
                {{fa-icon 'arrow-right'}}<a href="http://v3.sk/~naberacka/social_network_analysis_public_procurement_data_journalism.pdf">Read the thesis</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
